            id: "DO probe two-point calibration (zero + span)",
            issuer: "Mettler Toledo, Hamilton (bioprocess DO sensor method)",
            sources: "Mettler Toledo, Hamilton, PROAnalytics",
            covers: "Standard bioprocess DO calibration is two-point: zero current at 0% O₂ (calibrated first), then span at 100% air saturation. Method is consistent across the major probe makers; the control band is process-set.",
            crit: "Zero with N₂ purge (or sulfite) until the reading stabilizes (~10–30 min), then span in air-saturated medium. Verify the DO cascade (gas flow, agitation, O₂ enrichment) holds the setpoint band. The setpoint band (commonly 30–40% DO) is process-defined; confirm against the data sheet and process.",
            link: "https://www.hamiltoncompany.com/knowledge-base/article/do-sensor-calibration",
